The Presidential and National Assembly elections commenced early in Osun State and voters turned out in large numbers. At Ward 3, unit 10 and 11, Ataoja ‘C’ in Osogbo, the voters had begun to queue up as early as 7:30am. The officials of Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) and ad-hoc staff also arrived on time with election materials. At Ward 1, unit 3, St Peters, as well as unit 9, Isale-Afa, Ibokun, the voters trooped out in large numbers. #KogiDecides :Live Updates #Osun Decides2018 : Aregbesola expresses satisfaction over voting process APC,  PDP, SDP, ADC, others all found new ways to buy vote, say monitors